Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of WiMAX technology for broadband Internet networks and proposes a scheduling algorithm for UGS service class in WiMAX network. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on providing a satisfactory quality of experience (QoE) for multimedia services in WiMAX networks. This falls under the scope of multimedia.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of quality of experience (QoE) metrics for scheduling UGS connections in WiMAX networks. This falls under the scope of information theory.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly discuss security, but WiMAX networks are vulnerable to security threats and attacks. Therefore, this paper may also fall under the scope of cryptography and security.
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper does not explicitly discuss social and information networks, but the proposed scheduling algorithm can be applied to improve the QoE of users in social and information networks. Therefore, this paper may also fall under the scope of social and information networks.
